Parameter - Class in msquerybuilderbackend.entity
entity class of Parameter with getter and setter Parameter is an entity used in the entity ExpertQuery (also saved in neo4j database) and the QueryBuilder object the entity is relevant for saving the parameters to a queryString in the neo4j database but also to parse the QueryBuilder object and to interpret it
Parameter() - Constructor for class msquerybuilderbackend.entity.Parameter
 
ParameterRepository - Interface in msquerybuilderbackend.repository
Repository for Parameter objects in the neo4j database
postAlert(Alert) - Method in class msquerybuilderbackend.rest.AlertService
method which gets the POST-request and calls the alertBusiness method creates an alert in the neo4j database
postAuthority(String, String) - Method in class msquerybuilderbackend.rest.UserService
method which gets the POST-request for a specific user and calls the UserBusiness method creates a new user authority for the specific user
postCategory(Category) - Method in class msquerybuilderbackend.rest.CategoryService
method which gets the POST-request and calls the categoryBusiness method creates a new category in the neo4j database
postUser(User) - Method in class msquerybuilderbackend.rest.UserService
method which gets the POST-request and calls the UserBusiness method creates a User and its authority in the neo4j database
preExecuteQuery(ExpertQueryJsonObject) - Method in class msquerybuilderbackend.rest.ExpertQueryService
method which gets the POST-request and calls the ExpertQueryBusiness method executes a given ExpertQuery with parameters in the neo4j database
preExecuteQuery(QueryBuilder) - Method in class msquerybuilderbackend.rest.QueryBuilderService
method which gets the POST-request and calls the QueryBuilderBusiness method builds a query from the given QueryBuilder and executes it in the neo4j database
